<HL>
   Sony's Columbia Calls Debt
</HL>
<DATE>
04/30/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C14
</SO>
<CO>
   SNE
</CO>
<IN>
BOND MARKET NEWS (BON)
</IN>
<LP>
   NEW YORK -- Columbia Pictures Entertainment Inc. said it
called for redemption of about $279 million of senior debt,
to be repaid from funds provided by its parent Sony Corp. of
Japan.
   The entertainment company said it will redeem $250 million
of 10.625% senior subordinated debentures due 2018 at
108.717% of face value. It also will redeem $28.8 million of
14.5% senior subordinated debentures due 2000 at 107.25% of
face value. Columbia also will pay accrued interest to the
date of redemption on both issues. The securities will be
redeemed starting June 1, 1990.
